[ProMED-mail thanks Drs Grandadam and Souares for clarifying the
status of the chikungunya case reported in ProMED-mail archive number 20110708.2062 (and the dengue cases not reported in that post), and
providing information about the vigorous surveillance and vector
control efforts being carried out in Metropolitan France in those
areas where _Ae. albopictus_ is present. It was not clear in the
original report whether the chikungunya and dengue cases were locally
acquired or imported. Now we know that all were imported.
Establishment of _Ae. albopictus_ and its expansion is a significant
cause for concern and justifies the timely response of the public
health agencies in France to avoid the risk of ongoing virus
transmission.

A map of the departments of France can be accessed at
http://www.france-travel-info.com/maps-of-France.html. - Mod.TY]
